File: Eskom is urging customers to use electricity sparingly. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will implement Stage 2 load-shedding between 8am until 10pm on Saturday and Sunday. The power utility says it will help to refill its emergency generation reserves, ahead of next week. READ: SA sees worst power cuts on record in 2020, research shows On Friday the embattled company suspended two station managers pending disciplinary processes. The power utility's board and executive management met with Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan this week to discuss the causes of load-shedding and measures taken to repair breakdowns. Eskom is urging customers to use electricity sparingly.